The Kenya Kwanza Alliance on Monday took their Uchumi Kwanza, Pesa Mfukoni gospel to Busia county in a hunt for votes ahead of the general elections on August 9. Deputy President William Ruto, in the company of ANC party leader Musalia Mudavadi and Ford Kenya leader Moses Wetang'ula visited Butula, Ogalo, Funyula and Budalangi trading centres. They were accompanied by MPs Sakwa Bunyasi (Nambale), Malulu Injendi (Malava), Majimbo Kalasinga (Kabuchai), Cleophas malala (Kakamega), Ben Washiali (Mumias East), Ndindi Nyoro (Kiharu), Kasim Sawa Tandaza (Matuga), CAS - Ministry of Foreign Affairs Ababu Namwamba, UDA Party Chairman Johnson Muthama a host of MCA's and aspirants in Malaba and Nambale in Busia County. The trio is on a three-day charm offensive of the Western region which began in Vihiga on Sunday, during Mudavadi's homecoming. Ruto and his Kenya Kwanza Alliance brigade raided Vihiga county for a series of campaign rallies on Friday. The DP visited the area to grace Mudavadi's homecoming at Vihiga cultural grounds a fortnight after he declared willingness to work with him.